---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-mofu.njk",
  "permalink": "/about/network/",
  "slug": "network",
  "chrome": "full",
  "callBar": false,
  "tierClass": "section--tier-guide",
  "bodyClass": "page--mofu",
  "title": "ProAdvisor Network · How the Model Works · TechBrot",
  "description": "An independent lead practice plus vetted local Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors — one standard, one named point of accountability, and real continuity.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "About", "href": "/about/" },
    { "name": "The Network" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "How the platform works",
    "heading": "A platform, not a single firm.",
    "subheading": "TechBrot pairs an independent lead accounting practice with a curated network of vetted local Certified ProAdvisors &mdash; under one brand, one standard, and one named point of accountability. You get local expertise with platform-grade continuity. Here&rsquo;s exactly how it works.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=home", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Explore Services", "href": "/accounting/services/", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Local expertise, platform reliability",
    "heading": "Get matched to the right operator.",
    "lede": "Book a 30-minute discovery call. We&rsquo;ll scope what you need and match you to the lead practice or a vetted local operator &mdash; with a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=home", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "href": "tel:{{ site.phone.e164 }}", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-guide" id="network-tldr">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="tldr__heading">The model, plainly.</h2>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="network-tldr-body">TechBrot is a platform. The work gets delivered two ways: TechBrot&rsquo;s own lead practice handles engagements directly, and a curated network of vetted local Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors handles engagements in their own markets &mdash; all under TechBrot&rsquo;s brand, documented standards, and platform infrastructure. Every client gets a <strong>named point of accountability</strong>, works inside their <strong>own QuickBooks file</strong>, and is backed by <strong>platform-level continuity</strong> &mdash; so the relationship never depends on one individual staying available. The result is the thing most accounting buyers can&rsquo;t otherwise get at once: local expertise, real accountability, and institutional reliability.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="network-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The network model, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="network-flow">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How an engagement flows</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From your first call to clean books &mdash; through the platform.</h2>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for step in flow %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">0{{ loop.index }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ step.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ step.body | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="network-modes">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Two ways the work is delivered</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">One standard. Two delivery modes.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for mode in modes %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <p class="team-card__role">{{ mode.label }}</p>
        <h3>{{ mode.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ mode.body | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for li in mode.list %}<li>{{ li | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="{{ mode.href }}">{{ mode.cta }} &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source stack-8">In both modes you own your QuickBooks file and your data. The platform never locks you in &mdash; continuity is a feature, not a hostage.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="network-vetting">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The vetting bar</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Every operator clears the same bar.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Whether the work is delivered directly or by a network operator, the standard is identical &mdash; and reviewed on an ongoing basis, not just at intake.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for v in vetting %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>{{ v.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ v.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="network-compare">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Honest comparison</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A network beats the alternatives.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The rows where a competitor holds up are shown honestly &mdash; the model wins on continuity, standards, and accountability.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="vs-scroll">
      <table class="vs-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">How the TechBrot operator network compares to a solo bookkeeper, a remote subscription, and an offshore team.</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Dimension</th>
            <th scope="col" class="vs-table__us">TechBrot</th>
            {%- for c in compare.cols %}<th scope="col">{{ c }}</th>{%- endfor %}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {%- for row in compare.rows %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ row.dim | safe }}</td>
            <td class="vs-table__us"><strong>{{ row.us | safe }}</strong></td>
            {%- for o in row.others %}<td class="vs-table__concede">{{ o | safe }}</td>{%- endfor %}
          </tr>
          {%- endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="faq__more"><a href="/vs/">See all the side-by-side comparisons &rarr;</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="network-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Before you call</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Questions about the model.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="network-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="network-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="network-next">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Go deeper</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How the model shows up in practice.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for card in navCards %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>{{ card.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ card.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="{{ card.href }}">{{ card.cta }} &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
